com.vividsolutions.jcs.conflate.boundarymatch
Class MatchedShellSubject

java.lang.Object
  com.vividsolutions.jcs.conflate.boundarymatch.MatchedShell
      com.vividsolutions.jcs.conflate.boundarymatch.MatchedShellSubject
public class MatchedShellSubject
extends MatchedShell

A MatchedShell for features in the Subject dataset. Contains specific algorithms to compute the adjusted coordinates for a shell in a Subject dataset. Subject features may have both vertices added and existing vertices moved (to snap them to Reference vertices or lines).

createAdjustedVertexIndicator

public static com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate[] createAdjustedVertexIndicator(com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate origPt,
                                                                                     com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate adjustPt)
Create a vector that can be used to visually indicate the adjustment of a vertex. The vector is represented as a Coordinate array containing two elements. These can be converted to Geometry's using the CoordinateArrays.fromCoordinateArrays(java.util.List, com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.GeometryFactory) method.

Parameters:
origPt - the original location of the vertex
adjustPt - the location of the adjusted vertex
Returns:
a 2-point Coordinate array representing the adjustment vector

computeAdjustedShell

public void computeAdjustedShell()
Computes a new shell reflecting any adjustments made to segments and vertices. Adjusts (moves) any existing vertices that were adjusted. Also insert any new vertices that were added to segments.
